  <my:Hazards>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="1">
      <my:Description>Electricity</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Electric cable and its connections should not be submerged in water or other liquid; 
b) When connecting/disconnecting cables, switching on/off equipment hands should be dry; 
c) Do not use damaged equipment, improvised repairs of electrical tools must be avoided.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="2">
      <my:Description>Water - high pressure jet</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew should be instructed, briefed, following manufacturer’s operation manual; 
b) Use of PPE; 
c) Jet should never be directed at any part of human body.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="3">
      <my:Description>Debris - flying debris</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Use of PPE: goggles, face shield, gloves, safety shoes, etc.; 
b) Adequate illumination should be provided.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="4">
      <my:Description>Height - fall from</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>Consult ‘Working Aloft and Overboard’ Risk Assessment.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="5">
      <my:Description>Gas - lack of oxygen or hazardous vapours</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>Consult ‘Enclosed Space Entry’ Risk Assessment.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="6">
      <my:Description>Chemicals - skin irritation / chemical burns (e.g. when replenishing chemicals)</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>Consult ‘Dealing With Hazardous Substances’ Risk Assessment.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="7">
      <my:Description>Noise - from jet wash motor</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>2</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>3</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Consider use of ear defenders. 
b) More frequent breaks and job rotation must be considered to reduce the duration and effects associated with exposure; 
c) Ensure there is no wear &amp; tear or misalignment of components that could increase exposure levels. 
d) Consider other available work methods with less or no exposure effects that can be used to complete the task.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="8">
      <my:Description>Vibration - from jet wash lance</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>2</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>3</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Use gloves. 
b) More frequent breaks and job rotation must be considered to reduce the duration and effects associated with exposure; 
c) Ensure there is no wear &amp; tear or misalignment of components that could increase exposure levels. 
d) Consider other available work methods with less or no exposure effects that can be used to complete the task.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
